<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

Turn any tiddler into a //dashboard//: a free-form canvas onto which you drop other tiddlers as freely arrangeable tiles. Each tile transcludes a target tiddler; you move it, resize it, restyle it, and click it to open the underlying tiddler in the story river.

Tag a tiddler with <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard">> and a view-template body cascade entry swaps its body for the dashboard canvas — no special editor, no separate app.

!! Key features

* ''Drop to add'' — drag any tiddler from the wiki onto the canvas and it becomes a tile. Or type a title and press //Add tile//.
* ''Batch-add by filter'' — type any filter above the canvas and press //Add matching// to add a tile for each tiddler it selects, laid out in a grid.
* ''Clean'' — remove all tiles (or only those whose target matches a filter) in one confirmed step.
* ''Fit to screen'' — a per-dashboard toolbar toggle that scales the whole board down to fit your window (shrink-only), so everything is visible at once on a small display; dragging stays accurate while fitted.
* ''Fullscreen'' — a toolbar button that shows the dashboard fullscreen (whole screen, no wiki chrome); combine with //Fit to screen// to view the entire board at once.
* ''Free-form layout'' — absolute pixel positioning; drag a tile to move, drag its bottom-right corner to resize. Geometry is saved on release.
* ''Bring-to-front z-order'' — interacting with a tile raises it above the others; the stacking order persists.
* ''Two tile styles'' — a //window// tile with a title bar and controls, or a //bare// tile that is just the resizable content.
* ''Corner controls'' — a tile's controls appear in the corner on hover or keyboard focus. An ↗ open-external button (when the target has a link) sits beside the ⋮ //actions// menu, which holds ⧉ show-in-popup, ⊟ toggle window/bare, × remove.
* ''Attach a file — drop or paste'' — drop an image (or other media) onto a tile, or click the tile's 📋 corner button and press Ctrl+V to paste one from the clipboard. The file is uploaded to the filesystem location //derived from that tile's target//: a configured [[rimir/file-upload|$:/plugins/rimir/file-upload]] scattered location when the target's namespace matches one (e.g. a `work/…` target → the `work` location, alongside that item), otherwise the default `files` location — and it is added as a new tile beside the target. Dropping/pasting on a group (or in its canvas) files into the group's //context// location and adds a child; the plain canvas uses `files`. Needs the file-upload plugin.
* ''Choose what a tile shows'' — the body by default; uploaded images/PDFs show their thumbnail, and a tiddler with no text but an `icon` shows its icon. Override per tile (⋮ menu: auto / body / icon / any field), or per dashboard with filter-based //display rules//.
* ''Group (meta) tiles'' — a group tile is itself a free-form canvas you can drop other tiles into; groups nest recursively. Collapse/expand with ▸/▾, rename inline, and drag tiles (or whole groups) between containers to re-home them.
* ''Group context'' — link a group to a tiddler (⋮ menu → //Context…//, or drop a tiddler on its header) as its //implicit context//: the group adopts the tiddler's caption, shows its kind icon (click to open it), and — for a kind instance — offers the same ✎ //entity// actions as a content tile, creating children with `parent` set to the context //inside// this group.
* ''Collapse tiles'' — window tiles (and groups) collapse with a ▸/▾ toggle to just their headline, or to just their icon when one is defined. A collapsed tile still accepts drops (and clipboard paste): drop a tiddler/file onto a collapsed group (added as a child, then it expands), or a file onto a collapsed content tile (filed in the tile's derived location, as when open).
* ''Click to open'' — a click (as opposed to a drag) opens the tile's target tiddler in the story river; ''Ctrl/Cmd-click'' opens the target's external link (`url` / `_canonical_uri`, fields configurable) in a new browser tab. When the target has such a link, the tile's caption itself is rendered as a clickable link (opens in a new tab; hover shows the address in the status bar). A tile //without// an external link gets an ↗ item in its ⋮ menu that opens the target tiddler in a new tab via its permalink.
* ''Ctrl-drag to duplicate'' — hold Ctrl/Cmd while starting a drag to drop a copy of the tile elsewhere (the same tiddler may appear on any number of tiles).
* ''Show contents in a popup'' — the ⧉ control opens the target in a centered popup rendered through the default ViewTemplate (title, tags, fields and body), without leaving the dashboard.
* ''Kind-aware'' — when a tile's target is a [[rimir/kind|$:/plugins/rimir/kind]] instance, the window tile shows the type's icon (with the type name as hover text) before the caption. Silently absent when kind is not installed.
* ''Edit & extend kind entities'' — a kind-instance tile shows a ✎ //entity// control next to its ⋮ menu; hovering it opens a compact popup with //edit// (the same live editor modal as //Kind: Instances Overview//) and //Add child// buttons for every kind whose `parent` accepts this entity's type — the new child is also dropped as a tile into the same group as the source tile. Reuses the kind graph-modal; shown only when kind is installed.
* ''Plain-field storage'' — every tile is its own system tiddler with ordinary editable fields (`x`, `y`, `w`, `h`, `z`, `target`, `style`). No JSON blobs.

!! Quick start

# Click ''New dashboard'' in the page controls (right sidebar → Tools), or tag any tiddler <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard">>.
# Drag a few tiddlers onto the canvas.
# Move, resize, and restyle them; click one to open it.

See the ''Examples'' tab for concrete recipes and ''Reference'' for the full field and tag list.

